<font color="#FF0000">MAKING THE BEST OF THINGS</font><br>
<tt>Fri Dec 26 15:39:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Hope everyone's Christmas 1997 was wonderful.  Merry Christmas and Happy New Year to all.<br><br>
I want to know where Cook got the money on a preachers salary to buy all those gifts for MTF, and why all I got was a picture of a Virgin (even if it was a nice picture).  Thanks Cook.   We are talking of thousands of dollars here to buy the traditional 12 days of Christmas gifts.  Mainly because the cost for finding royalty willing to go around leaping even if you can find any anymore has skyrocketed.  As soon as I got myself extricated from the deep cow dung MTF and I started thinking how we could best turn around a messy situation.  We held a winter festival at the local park that was more than willing to accept the swans as a contribution and allow us free usage of the park for the festival (Admission price $7.00 , part of the proceeds to go to help homeless veterans.).  The festival was a great success.   Everyone wanted to buy milkshakes made with milk they had pumped themselves with instruction from the milking maids.  The dancing ladies were available for dance lessons. Watch out Arthur Murry. The drummers and pipers got together and formed a big band.  You know how it is, most musicians know how to play more than one musical instrument and these guys and gals were good!   We sold goose eggs to the handcrafters who pay about $5 for each goose egg to make Easter decorations and those fancy egg boxes.  We asked the lords to stop that ridiculous leaping and whether they wouldn't prefer to go out on a date with some of the local professional women.  They agreed so there was a charity auction for an evening with British royalty.   There were bird calling, cow milking and dancing contests.  The maids a milking have had their jobs changed to house cleaning now that the festival is over, and although they complained at first they all agreed that $40  for 2-4 hours of work at each house they cleaned after job training at ours would be an upwardly mobile step. Milking machines have been rightsizing the dairy industry and they have been having more and more difficulty finding work.  Mrs. MTF will provide administrative oversight for the newly incorporated corporation called Merry Maids.    Social Security gets their cut of the salaries so the INS was happy to issue the gals green cards.  <br><br>
The fertilizer got spread and next year there should be a great harvest in time for thanksgiving.  Everyone who is still around has started to sculpt the remaining  shit  into interesting animal shapes after sterilizing what was left and plan on giving the Amish a run for their money on dried garden pets. <br><br>
As MTF has already stated, he has enough feathers now to keep the tribe in war bonnets for the next ten years and dibbies on any swan feathers found at the park.  MTF also kept the golden rings. He is wearing one to remember Cook's 1997 Christmas present and had the other four made into hoop earring for his wife and daughter.   Forget the law-suit.  Everyone seems happy again.<br><br>
Whether something is a disaster or a blessing is all in the way you look at it.<br><br>
PS  I don't know if any of you have heard Garth Brooks new CD called SEVENS.  If you haven't let me suggest you listen to his last song on that album called Belleau Woods.  It is a song about Christmas in the trenches (I believe during WWI) when a truce was called.  
<p><code>--   (Class Lass) </code><p>


